description.p:
According to aspects of the invention, there can be provided an electronically controlled throttle device according to one or more of the following clauses:
Clause 1: An electronically controlled throttle device, comprising:
a throttle body (1) having a throttle valve housing section (10) and a motor housing section (31) which are integrally molded;
a DC motor (3) put in the motor housing section of said throttle body to drive said throttle valve;
a power transmission unit (4) arranged on said throttle body (1) to transmit a driving power from said DC motor (3) to said throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on said throttle body (1) to protect said DC motor (3) and said power transmission unit (4); and
an inductance (45a, 45b) installed on an inner surface of said cover (40) and connected with said DC motor (3) and a power supply through conductors (44).
clause 2: An electronically controlled throttle device, comprising:
a throttle body (1) having a throttle valve housing section (10) and a motor housing section (31) which are integrally molded with an insulating material;
a DC motor (3) put in the motor housing section (31) of said throttle body (1) to drive said throttle valve (1);
a power transmission unit (4) with gears arranged on said throttle body (1) to transmit a driving power from said DC motor (3) to said throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on said throttle body (1) to protect said DC motor (3) and said power transmission unit (4); and
an inductance (45a, 45b) installed on an inner surface of said cover (40), wherein one end of said inductance (45a, 45b) is connected with said DC motor (3) through one conductor (44) buried in said cover, and another end thereof is connected with a power supply through another conductor (44) buried in said cover (40).
Clause 3: An electronically controlled throttle device, comprising:
a throttle body (1) having an external wall section for a gear space, a throttle valve housing section (10) and a motor housing section (31) which are integrally molded with an insulating material ;
a DC motor (3) put in the motor housing of said throttle body (1) to drive said throttle valve (2) and controlled by electrical throttle devices;
a power transmission unit (4) configured with gears which are arranged on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) to transmit a driving power from said DC motor (3) to said throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) so as to cover said DC motor (3) and said power transmission unit (4);
a connector (43) provided on an outer surface of said cover (40) to electrically connect with an external unit and having a plurality of terminals (43a) including a power supply terminal for said DC motor (3); and
an inductance (45a, 45b) installed on an inner surface of said cover (40), wherein one end of said inductance (45a, 45b) is connected with said power supply terminal through one conductor (44) buried in said cover (40), and another end thereof is connected with said DC motor (3) through another conductor (40) buried in said cover (44).
Clause 4: An electronically controlled throttle device, comprising:
a throttle body (1) having an external wall section for a gear space, a throttle valve housing section (10) and a motor housing section (31) which are integrally molded with an insulating material;
a DC motor (3) put in the motor housing of said throttle body (1) to drive said throttle valve (2) and controlled by electrical throttle devices;
a power transmission unit (4) configured with gears which are arranged on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) to transmit a driving power from said DC motor (3) to said throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on an external wall section of said throttle body (1) so as to cover said DC motor (3) and said power transmission unit (4);
a connector (43) provided on an outer surface of said cover (40) to electrically connect with an external unit and having
a plurality of terminals (43a) including a power supply terminal for said DC motor (3);
an intermediate connector (42) with a joint member connected to said power supply terminal through a conductor (44) buried in said cover (40), and connected to a terminal of said DC motor (3) through said joint member when said cover (40) is attached on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) ; and
an inductance (45a, 45b) installed on an inner surface of said cover (40), wherein one end of said inductance (45a, 45b) is connected with said power supply terminal through one conductor (44) buried in said cover (40), and another end thereof is connected with said intermediate terminal (42) through another conductor (44) buried in said cover (40).
clause 5: An electronically controlled throttle device, comprising:
a throttle body (1) having an external wall section for a gear space, a throttle valve housing section (10) and a motor housing section (31) which are integrally molded with an insulating material;
a DC motor (3) put in the motor housing of said throttle body (1) to drive said throttle valve (2) and controlled by electrical throttle devices;
a power transmission unit (4) configured with gears which are arranged on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) to transmit a driving power from said DC motor (3) to said throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on an external wall section of said throttle body so as to cover said DC motor (3) and said power transmission unit (4);
a connector (43) provided on an outer surface of said cover (40) to electrically connect with an external unit and having a plurality of terminals (43a) including two power supply terminals for said DC motor (3);
an intermediate connector (42) with joint members connected to said power supply terminals through conductors buried in said cover (40), and connected to terminals of said DC motor side through said joint members when said cover (40) is attached on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) ;
an inductance housing formed by providing a partitioning plate on an inner surface of said cover (45); and
a noise eliminator configured with two inductances (45a) placed in said inductance housing, wherein one end of each inductance (45a) is connected with each power supply terminal through conductor (44) buried in said cover (40), and another end thereof is connected with each terminal of said intermediate connector (42) through said conductor (44). Clause 6: The electronically controlled throttle device according to any of clauses 1 to 5, wherein said inductance (45a) is covered by gel.
Clause 7:An electronically controlled throttle device, comprising:
a throttle body (1) having an external wall section for a gear space, a throttle valve housing section (10) and a motor housing section (31) which are integrally molded with an insulating material ;
a DC motor (3) put in the motor housing of said throttle body (1) to drive said throttle valve (2) and controlled by electrical throttle devices;
a power transmission unit (4) configured with gears which are arranged on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) to transmit a driving power from said DC motor (3) to said throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) so as to cover said DC motor (3) and said power transmission unit (4);
a connector (43) provided on an outer surface of said cover (40) to electrically connect with an external unit and having a plurality of terminals (43a) including a power supply terminal for said DC motor (3);
an electronic control module (11) placed in a module housing section provided at said cover to control said throttle valve (2), and to which DC voltage is supplied from said power supply terminal of said connector (43); and
an inductance (45a, 45b) installed on an inner surface of said cover (40), wherein one end of said inductance (45a, 45b) is connected with each motor driving terminal of said electronic control module (11) through one conductor (44) buried in said cover (40), and another end thereof is connected with said DC motor through another conductor (44).
Clause 8:An electronically controlled throttle device, comprising:
a throttle body (1) having an external wall section for a gear space, a throttle valve housing section (10) and a motor housing section (31) which are integrally molded with an insulating material ;
a DC motor (3) put in the motor housing of said throttle body to drive said throttle valve (2) and controlled by electrical throttle devices;
a power transmission unit (4) configured with gears which are arranged on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) to transmit a driving power from said DC motor (3) to said throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) so as to cover said DC motor (3) and said power transmission unit (4);
a connector (40) provided on an outer surface of said cover (40) to electrically connect with an external unit and having a plurality of terminals (43a) including a power supply terminal for said DC motor (3);
an electronic control module (11) placed in a module housing section provided at said cover to control said throttle valve (2), and to which DC voltage is supplied from said power supply terminal of said connector (43);
an intermediate connector (42) with joint members connected to terminals of said DC motor side when said cover is attached on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) ;
an inductance (45a, 45b) installed near to said electronic control module on an inner surface of said cover (40), wherein one end of said inductance (45a, 45b) is connected with a motor driving terminal provided at said electronic control module (11) through one conductor (44) buried in said cover (40), and another end thereof is connected with said intermediate connector (42) through said another conductor (44) buried in said cover (40).
clause 9:An electronically controlled throttle device, comprising:
a throttle body (1) having an external wall section for a gear space, a throttle valve housing section (10) and a motor housing section (31) which are integrally molded with an insulating material ;
a DC motor (3) put in the motor housing of said throttle body (1) to drive said throttle valve (2);
a power transmission unit (4) configured with gears which are arranged on said external wall section of said throttle body (1) to transmit a driving power from said DC motor (3) to said throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on said external wall section of said throttle body so as to cover said DC motor (3) and said power transmission unit (4);
a connector (43) provided on an outer surface of said cover (40) to electrically connect with an external unit and having a plurality of terminals (43a) including two power supply terminals for said DC motor (3);
an electronic control module (11) placed in a module housing section provided at said cover to control said throttle valve (2), and to which DC voltage is supplied from said power supply terminals (43a) of said connector (43), and having two motor driving terminals,
an intermediate connector (42) with joint members provided on inner surface of said cover (40), and having two terminals connected to terminals of DC motor side through said joint member when said cover (40) is attached on said external wall section of said throttle body (1);
a noise eliminator configured with two inductances (45a, 45b) placed in parallel near to said module housing section on inner surface of said cover (40), wherein one end of each inductance (45a, 45b) is connected with each motor driving terminal of said electronic control module through one conductor (44) buried in said cover (40), and another end thereof is connected with each terminal of said intermediate connector (42) through another conductor (44) buried in said cover (40).
Clause 10: The electronically controlled throttle device according to any one of clauses 7 to 9, wherein said electronic control module (11) and said inductance (45a, 45b) are covered by gel.
Clause 11: The electronically controlled throttle device according to any one of clauses 1 to 10, wherein each one end of said conductors (44) protrudes near to the inductance on the inner surface of said cover (40), and such protruding ends of said conductors (44) hold both ends of said inductance (45a, 45b).

claim.claim-text:
Elektronisch gesteuerte Drosselvorrichtung mit:
einem Drosselkörper (1) mit einem Drosselventil-Gehäuseabschnitt (10) für ein Drosselventil (2) und einem Motorgehäuseabschnitt (31) für einen Gleichstrommotor (3) als Drosselventilaktor, wobei der Drosselventil-Gehäuseabschnitt und der Motorgehäuseabschnitt miteinander einstückig geformt sind;
dem Gleichstrommotor (3), der zum Antreiben des Drosselventils (2) in den Motorgehäuseabschnitt (10) des Drosselkörpers (1) gesetzt ist;
einem Verzögerungszahnradmechanismus (4), der auf einem äußeren Wandabschnitt (12) des Drosselkörpers (1) als Leistungsübertragungseinheit angeordnet ist, um eine Antriebsleistung vom Gleichstrommotor (3) auf das Drosselventil (2) zu übertragen;
einer am äußeren Wandabschnitt (12) des Drosselkörpers (1) angebrachten Abdeckung (40), um den Gleichstrommotor (3) und den Verzögerungszahnradmechanismus (4) zu schützen;
einem Konnektor (43) zum Verbinden mit einer externen Einheit;
einem konnektorseitigen Leiter, damit er Teil eines Leiters (44) ist, wobei der konnektorseitige Leiter in der Wand der Abdeckung (40) verborgen ist, die mit dem Konnektor (43) an einem Ende verbunden werden soll;
einem Zwischenkonnektor (42) mit einem angefügten Element, das an den Konnektor (43) durch den in der Abdeckung (40 verborgenen Leiter (44) anschließbar ist und an einen Anschluss des Gleichstrommotors (3) durch das angefügte Element angeschlossen ist, wenn die Abdeckung (40) an dem äußeren Wandabschnitt des Drosselkörpers (1) angebracht ist;
einem konnektorseitigen Zwischenleiter, so dass er Teil des Leiters (44) ist, wobei der in einer Wand der Abdeckung (40) verborgene zwischenseitige Leiter mit dem Zwischenkonnektor (42) an einem Ende verbunden werden soll; und dadurch gekennzeichnet, dass
eine Induktivität (45) zwischen dem konnektorseitigen Zwischenleiter und dem konnektorseitigen Leiter so angeordnet ist, dass sie mit dem konnektorseitigen Zwischenleiter und dem konnektorseitigen Leiter in Reihe geschaltet ist, wobei die Induktivität (45) auf der Innenseite der Abdeckung (40) befestigt ist,
wobei die Induktivität (45) in einem Raum vorgesehen ist, der mit der Innenseite der Abdeckung (40) und dem äußeren Wandabschnitt (12) des Drosselkörpers (1) bei Anbringung der Abdeckung (40) am Drosselkörper (1) umschlossen ist.

An electronically controlled throttle device comprising:
a throttle body (1) having a throttle valve housing section (10) for a throttle valve (2) and a motor housing section (31) for a DC motor (3) as a throttle valve actuator, the throttle valve housing section and the motor housing section being integrally molded with each other;
the DC motor (3) put in the motor housing section (10) of the throttle body (1) to drive the throttle valve (2);
a deceleration gear mechanism (4) arranged on an external wall section (12) of the throttle body (1) as a power transmission unit to transmit a driving power from the DC motor (3) to the throttle valve (2);
a cover (40) attached on the external wall section (12) of the throttle body (1) to protect the DC motor (3) and the deceleration gear mechanism (4);
a connector (43) for connecting to an external unit;
a connector- side conductor to be a part of a conductor (44), the connector-side conductor buried in the wall of the cover (40) to be connected to the connector (43) at one end;
an intermediate connector (42) with a joint member connectable to said connector (43) through the conductor (44) buried in said cover (40), and connected to a terminal of said DC motor (3) through said joint member when said cover (40) is attached on said external wall section of said throttle body (1);
an intermediate connector-side conductor to be a part of the conductor (44), the intermediate-side conductor buried in a wall of the cover (40) to be connected to the intermediate connector (42) at one end; and characterized in that,
an inductance (45) is arranged between the intermediate connector-side conductor and the connector side-conductor so as to be electrically connected to the intermediate connector-side conductor and the connector side-conductor in series, the inductance (45) fixed on an inner surface of the cover (40),
wherein the inductance (45) is provided in a space enclosed with the inner surface of the cover (40) and the external wall section (12) of the throttle body (1) upon attachment of the cover (40) to the throttle body (1).

Dispositif formant papillon à commande électronique, comprenant :
un corps de papillon (1) ayant une section de boîtier de vanne papillon (10) pour une vanne papillon (2) et une section de carter de moteur (31) pour un moteur à courant continu (3) à titre d'actionneur de vanne papillon, la section de boîtier de vanne papillon et la section de carter de moteur étant moulées intégralement l'une avec l'autre ;
le moteur à courant continu (3) disposé dans la section de carter de moteur (10) du corps de papillon pour entraîner la vanne papillon (2) ;
un mécanisme à engrenages de décélération (4) agencé sur une section de paroi extérieure (12) du corps de papillon (1) à titre d'unité de transmission de puissance pour transmettre une puissance d'entraînement depuis le moteur à courant continu (3) à la vanne papillon (2) ;
un couvercle (40) attaché sur la section de paroi extérieure (12) du corps de papillon (1) pour protéger le moteur à courant continu (3) et le mécanisme à engrenages de décélération (4) ;
un connecteur (43) pour la connexion à une unité externe ;
un conducteur côté connecteur destiné à faire partie d'un conducteur (44), le conducteur côté connecteur étant noyé dans la paroi du couvercle (40) pour être connecté au connecteur (43) à une extrémité ;
un connecteur intermédiaire (42) avec un élément de jonction susceptible d'être connecté audit connecteur (43) via le conducteur (44) noyé dans ledit couvercle (40), et connecté à une borne dudit moteur à courant continu (3) via ledit élément de jonction quand ledit couvercle (40) est attaché sur ladite section de paroi extérieure dudit corps de papillon (1) ;
un conducteur côté connecteur intermédiaire destiné à faire partie du conducteur (44), le conducteur côté intermédiaire étant noyé dans une paroi du couvercle (40) pour être connecté au connecteur intermédiaire (42) à une extrémité ; et
caractérisé en ce que
une inductance (45) est agencée entre le conducteur intermédiaire côté connecteur et le conducteur côté connecteur de manière à être électriquement connectée au conducteur intermédiaire côté connecteur et au conducteur côté connecteur en série, l'inductance (45) étant fixée sur une surface intérieure du couvercle (40),
dans lequel l'inductance (45) est prévue dans un espace enfermé avec la surface intérieure du couvercle (40) et la section de paroi extérieure (12) du corps de papillon (1) lorsque le couvercle (40) est attaché sur le corps de papillon (1).
